## Summary Table: Effects of Social Media on Communication and Behavior

| Aspect                        | Positive Effects                                            | Negative Effects                                               |
|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------|
| Communication Style            | Concise, efficient messaging; global reach                  | Reduced face-to-face interaction; loss of nonverbal cues       |
| Language Use                  | New forms of expression (emojis, GIFs)                      | Decline in formal writing and literacy skills                  |
| Emotional Connection          | Maintains long-distance relationships                       | Emotional superficiality; increased loneliness and depression |
| Personal Relationships        | Facilitates new connections and support                     | Erosion of trust; increased deception and jealousy             |
| Attention and Focus           | Quick information access                                    | Shortened attention spans; distraction                         |
| Social Behavior               | Broadened social networks; activism                          | Online disinhibition; cyberbullying                            |
| Identity and Self-Perception  | Platforms for self-expression                                | Validation dependency; curated personas                        |

